nodes.bodyText: Yeah, sounds good. Testing it on 3.5.4 led to some elements being in non-deterministic order, so I fixed up the Dataframe equality logic to also do a sort. Though interestingly enough this passes on later version of Python. This is probably because the dict ordering respects insertion ordering on later version, 3.6+ if I'm not mistaken.
